      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🔴 Critical Issues] Line 85: Race condition: notePushReceived() posts the grace timestamp update to the main handler but does not cancel an already-due deactivateRunnable. If a background push arrives around the 5s deactivation deadline, the old runnable can run before this posted update, enqueue account deactivation after the FCM path has restored accounts, and interrupt push/call handling. Move the timestamp update and rescheduling into one main-thread operation, or cancel the pending runnable before posting. For example:\n```suggestion\nfun notePushReceived(isCallPush: Boolean) {\n    val now \u003d SystemClock.elapsedRealtime()\n    backgroundHandler.post {\n        backgroundHandler.removeCallbacks(deactivateRunnable)\n        lastPushTime \u003d now\n        if (isCallPush) lastCallPushTime \u003d now\n        scheduleBackgroundDeactivation()\n    }\n}\n```",
